+### Dashboard
+
+```
+hermes dashboard [--port PORT] [--host HOST] [--no-open] [--insecure] [--tui] [--stop] [--status]
+```
+
+Browser-based management UI (FastAPI + Vite/React SPA). Requires `pip install hermes-agent[web]` (FastAPI, Uvicorn).
+
+- **Default:** `http://127.0.0.1:9119`
+- **`--insecure`**: bind to `0.0.0.0` — **DANGEROUS**: exposes API keys on the network. Only use behind a reverse proxy or VPN.
+- **GZip patch** (source-level): dashboard serves ~1.2MB JS uncompressed. Adding `GZipMiddleware` to `web_server.py` cuts transfer ~3.4×. See `references/dashboard-gzip-and-provider-cleanup.md` for the patch and verification steps.
+- **`--tui`**: expose an in-browser Chat tab (embedded `hermes --tui` via PTY/WebSocket). Also set via `HERMES_DASHBOARD_TUI=1`.
+- **`--stop`**: kill all running dashboard processes and exit.
+- **`--status`**: list running dashboard processes and exit.
+- **Performance pitfall:** if the SPA feels slow over Tailscale, check static asset compression. Case note: `references/dashboard-provider-cleanup-ollama-cloud-2026-05-10.md` covers GZip verification and the bundle-size symptom.
+- **OpenAI Codex model picker pitfall:** if Dashboard shows fewer Codex models than `config.yaml`, first check `/api/model/options`; the fix pattern is curated defaults + live discovery merge, `provider_model_ids("openai-codex")`, config-model merge, and dashboard restart. Case note: `references/dashboard-openai-codex-model-picker-2026-05-10.md`.
+
+Auth: session token generated on start, embedded in SPA HTML. Public API paths (no auth): `/api/status`, `/api/config/defaults`, `/api/config/schema`, `/api/model/info`, `/api/dashboard/themes`, `/api/dashboard/plugins`.
+
+Sections: **Config** (edit config.yaml + .env via web), **Sessions** (browse/search/delete), **Analytics** (tokens, cost, cache hit%, per-model breakdown for 7/30/90 days), **Skills & Toolsets** (toggle on/off), **Model Info** (context length, provider), **Gateway** (restart, platform status), **Chat** (if `--tui`).
+
+7 built-in themes: default (Hermes Teal), default-large, midnight, ember, mono, cyberpunk, rosé. Configurable via `config.yaml` `dashboard.theme`.
+
+Remote access: use `ssh -L 9119:127.0.0.1:9119 user@host` or Tailscale. Do NOT use `--insecure` on public networks.
