+### Hermes Dashboard
+
+`hermes dashboard` launches a FastAPI + Vite/React web UI for managing config, sessions, skills, and analytics.
+
+**Startup:**
+```bash
+hermes dashboard                       # http://127.0.0.1:9119
+hermes dashboard --port 8080           # custom port
+hermes dashboard --host 0.0.0.0 --insecure --no-open  # network-wide (exposes API keys!)
+```
+
+- Requires `pip install hermes-agent[web]` (FastAPI + Uvicorn). Pre-built frontend ships in `hermes_cli/web_dist/`.
+- Default binds `127.0.0.1:9119`. Refuses non-localhost without `--insecure` because the dashboard exposes API keys/config without robust auth.
+- Auth: session token generated at startup, embedded in HTML. `/api/` routes (except public subset: `/api/status`, `/api/config/defaults`, `/api/config/schema`, `/api/model/info`, `/api/dashboard/themes`, `/api/dashboard/plugins`) require the token cookie.
+
+**Remote access (phone / other devices):**
+
+1. **SSH tunnel (recommended):** `ssh -L 9119:127.0.0.1:9119 user@VPS-IP` → `http://localhost:9119`
+2. **Tailscale direct:** `hermes dashboard --host 0.0.0.0 --insecure --no-open` + `sudo ufw allow in on tailscale0 to any port 9119 proto tcp` → `http://<tailscale-IP>:9119`
+
+**Pitfall:** UFW default policy is DROP. Even with `--host 0.0.0.0`, the port must be opened explicitly. For Tailscale-only access use `on tailscale0` in the ufw rule to avoid exposing the dashboard to the public internet.
+
+**Pitfall:** The `--insecure` flag is required for non-localhost binding. Without it Hermes refuses to start: *"Refusing to bind to <IP> — the dashboard exposes API keys and config without robust authentication."*
+
+**Pitfall:** Dashboard SPA ships a ~1.2 MB JS bundle and ~95 KB CSS without compression. On slower connections (Tailscale relay, mobile) this makes the dashboard feel sluggish on first load. Add `GZipMiddleware` to `hermes_cli/web_server.py` after the CORS middleware block to compress responses ≥500 bytes:
+
+```python
+from starlette.middleware.gzip import GZipMiddleware
+app.add_middleware(GZipMiddleware, minimum_size=500)
+```
+
+This reduces the JS bundle from ~1.2 MB to ~350 KB (×3.4) and CSS from ~95 KB to ~15 KB (×6.2). Requires dashboard process restart. This patch will need reapplying after `hermes update`.
+
+**Key API endpoints** (session cookie required except public ones listed above):
+- `GET /api/status` — version, gateway state, platforms, active sessions
+- `GET /api/sessions?limit=N&offset=N` — session list with metadata
+- `GET /api/sessions/search?q=...` — text search
+- `GET /api/config` — current config (sanitized); `POST /api/config` — update
+- `GET /api/config/defaults` — defaults; `GET /api/config/schema` — UI schema
+- `GET /api/model/info` — model, provider, context length, capabilities
+- `POST /api/model/set` — assign provider/model to a slot
+- `GET /api/dashboard/themes` — available UI themes (default, midnight, ember, mono, cyberpunk, rosé, default-large); set via `dashboard.theme` in config.yaml
+- `GET /api/dashboard/plugins` — installed plugins
+- `POST /api/gateway/restart` — restart gateway
+- `POST /api/hermes/update` — trigger hermes update
